(April 22, 1960) In the Matter of Mayo Cabey, Respondent, against New York City Employees’ Retirement System, Respondent, and Consuelo Cabey, Appellant.

(Republished)

Appeals from orders of February 11, 1959 and February 27, 1959 and decision of -March 31, 1959, unanimously dismissed as they have been reviewed on the appeal from the final order and are not otherwise appealable. (See Matter of Cabey v. New York City Employees’ Retirement System, 10 A D 2d 836.) Concur — Breitel, J. P., M. M. Frank, Valente, Stevens and Bergan, JJ.
